<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 - Page Not Found</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f7fa 0%, #c3cfe2 100%);
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            text-align: center;
            max-width: 600px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
            box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 4em;
            color: #E91E63;
            margin: 0 0 10px;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 1.5em;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #009688;
            font-size: 1.2em;
        }
        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 300px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body> 

    <div class="container">
        <h1>404</h1>
        <p>Oh no! The page you're looking for can't be found.</p>
        <a href="/">GO BACK TO HOME</a>
        <img src="https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/404-error-with-landscape-concept-illustration_114360-7898.jpg" alt="Funny 404 Error Image" />
    </div>
</body>
</html>
